#### Fix B2 — Missing Return Statements in Controllers (Requirement 5)

The following controllers have conditional `res.status(...).json(...)` calls **without** a preceding `return`, causing potential "headers already sent" crashes when execution falls through.

**Files and specific locations:**

**`matasree-backend/src/controllers/cartController.ts`**

In `addToCart`:
```typescript
// BEFORE
if (!productId || !quantity || quantity < 1) {
  res.status(400).json(new ApiResponse(false, 'Invalid product or quantity', null, 400));
}
// AFTER
if (!productId || !quantity || quantity < 1) {
  return res.status(400).json(new ApiResponse(false, 'Invalid product or quantity', null, 400));
}
```

Apply the same pattern to every early-exit `res` call in `updateCartItem` and `removeFromCart`.

**`matasree-backend/src/controllers/categoryController.ts`**

`getCategoryById`, `createCategory`, `updateCategory`, `deleteCategory` — add `return` before every `res.status(404)` and `res.status(400)` call inside conditional branches.

**`matasree-backend/src/controllers/orderController.ts`**

`createOrder`, `verifyPayment`, `updateOrderStatus` — add `return` before every early-exit `res` call. Example:
```typescript
// BEFORE
if (error) {
  res.status(400).json(new ApiResponse(false, error.details[0].message, null, 400));
}
// AFTER
if (error) {
  return res.status(400).json(new ApiResponse(false, error.details[0].message, null, 400));
}
```

**`matasree-backend/src/controllers/partnershipController.ts`**

`submitPartnershipApplication`, `getPartnershipApplicationById`, `updatePartnershipStatus` — add `return` before every conditional `res.status(...)` call.

**`matasree-backend/src/controllers/productController.ts`**

`createProduct`, `updateProduct`, `deleteProduct` — `return` before every early-exit `res` call in validation branches.

**Note on `addressController.ts`:** The existing code already uses `return res.status(...)` consistently; no changes needed.

