#### Fix B3 — Auth Controller: issueTokens Type Mismatch (Requirement 6)

**File:** `matasree-backend/src/controllers/authController.ts`

In `oauthCallback`, the `meta` object is passed as `as any`. This is not needed because `authService.issueTokens` already accepts `meta?: { userAgent?: string; ipAddress?: string }`, and `req.headers['user-agent']` is `string | string[] | undefined`. A simple cast to `string | undefined` is sufficient and type-safe.

**Change:**
```typescript
// BEFORE
const { accessToken } = await issueTokens(user, res, {
  userAgent: req.headers['user-agent'] as string,
  ipAddress: req.ip,
} as any);

// AFTER — remove the outer "as any"; cast only the header value
const { accessToken } = await issueTokens(user, res, {
  userAgent: req.headers['user-agent'] as string | undefined,
  ipAddress: req.ip,
});
```

`authService.ts` already types `meta.userAgent` as `string | undefined` — no changes needed there.

