#### Fix C3 — Password Reset OTP: Preserve Across Verify Step (Requirement 8)

**File:** `matasree-backend/src/controllers/authController.ts`

The current `verifyPasswordResetOtp` deletes the OTP entry (`delete passwordResetOtpStore[email]`) on success. This means `resetPassword` cannot find the OTP. The fix is to not delete the entry in the verify step — `resetPassword` already deletes it after use.

```typescript
// BEFORE — verifyPasswordResetOtp (last 3 lines of the success path)
if (stored.otp !== otp) { stored.attempts++; return res.status(400)... }

delete passwordResetOtpStore[email];   // ← BUG: deletes before resetPassword can use it
res.status(200).json(new ApiResponse(true, 'OTP verified successfully'));

// AFTER — remove the delete; resetPassword handles cleanup
if (stored.otp !== otp) { stored.attempts++; return res.status(400)... }

// Do NOT delete here — resetPassword will consume and delete the entry
res.status(200).json(new ApiResponse(true, 'OTP verified successfully'));
```

`resetPassword` already contains the correct logic: it verifies the OTP and then calls `delete passwordResetOtpStore[email]`. No change needed there.

