#### Fix D4 — AddressesPage: Fix Double Data Unwrapping (Requirement 15)

**File:** `matasree-superstore-main/src/pages/AddressesPage.tsx`

The response interceptor in `api.ts` unwraps `response.data` to the top level. So the `useAddresses` hook data already contains `{ success, data: [...addresses], statusCode }`. The current code accesses `addressesData.data?.data` which is one level too deep.

```tsx
// BEFORE
const addresses = useMemo(() => {
  if (!addressesData) return [];
  const data = addressesData.data?.data || addressesData.data?.addresses || addressesData.data || [];
  return Array.isArray(data) ? data : [];
}, [addressesData]);

// AFTER — the interceptor already unwraps once; backend returns { success, data: [...] }
const addresses = useMemo(() => {
  if (!addressesData) return [];
  // addressesData is the already-unwrapped ApiResponse: { success, data: [...], message }
  const data = addressesData.data || [];
  return Array.isArray(data) ? data : [];
}, [addressesData]);
```

